Kim Cheatle has been selected as the next Director of the United States Secret Service. She has had a long and distinguished career at the Secret Service, rising through the ranks over her 27 years with the agency. She was the first woman to hold the role of Assistant Director of protective operations. President Biden and Jill Biden have personally worked with Cheatle and trust her judgment and counsel. Cheatle is a distinguished law enforcement professional with exceptional leadership skills. She has been awarded the Presidential Rank Award for exceptional performance. Currently, Cheatle is a senior director at PepsiCo North America, overseeing facilities, personnel, and business continuity. She has previously served in various leadership roles within the Secret Service, including overseeing the Office of Protective Operations. Cheatle has also served as the Special Agent in Charge of the Atlanta Field Office.